title: Connie Willis - The Last of the Winnebagos
description:
Hugo Award for Best Novella (1989)
Nebula Award for Best Novella (1989)
Locus Award Nominee for Best Novella (1989)
SF Chronicle Award for Best Novella (1989)
Asimov's Readers' Poll Award for Best Novella (1989)

In this Hugo Award-winning novella, dogs have become extinct after an epidemic, and the Humane Society has been granted extraordinary police powers to protect the remaining animals.

As the Society investigates the death of a jackal on a highway, its attention turns to a photojournalist whose own dog was one of the last to survive.

Read by Dennis Boutsikaris (Narrator)
Format: MP3
Bitrate: 64 Kbps
Unabridged
